cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the performance of in-band full duplex communication in cellular networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper derives a closed form expression of the maximum achievable uplink capacity, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the interference problem in cellular networks, which is a communication topic. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the performance of a system (cellular network) with different parameters, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - Although not the main focus, the paper mentions the impact of full duplex communication on the downlink performance, which is related to multimedia applications.
